Now, on the other hand, from the problem statement, we know that the NPV index is given by the following formula:

$$
\begin{align}
\text{NPV}_\text I = \dfrac{\text{NPV}}{\text{Cost}}
\end{align}
$$
We can observe from Equation 2 that the NPV index is a measure of the degree of profitability (or unprofitability) of an investment in relation to its cost.

Then, we'll analyze the Profitability Index (PI). PI is defined as the ratio of present value to cost, for a given investment. It can thus be calculated using the following formula:
$$
\begin{align}
\text{PI} = \dfrac{\text{PV}}{\text{Cost}} = \dfrac{\sum_{i=1}^{t} \frac{\text{CF}_i}{(1+\text{r})^i}}{\text{Initial investment}}
\end{align}
$$
From Equation 5, we can observe that the Profitability Index is also an indicator of a project's degree of profitability or lack thereof.
